<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?id=1193" title="The Case for Impeachment"> The Case for Impeachment</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p>In the March 2006 issue of Harper&#8217;s magazine, Lewis Lapham writes the essay <a href="http://harpers.org/TheCaseForImpeachment.html">The Case for Impreachment</a>. It takes a gander at the 182-page report created by the office of U.S. Rep. John Conyers entitled &#8220;The Constitution in Crisis; The Downing Street Minutes and Deception, Manipulation, Torture, Retribution, and Coverups in the Iraq War.” His conclusion?</p>
	<blockquote>
		<p>&#8220;Before reading the report, I wouldn&#8217;t have expected to find myself thinking that such a course of action was either likely or possible; after reading the report, I don&#8217;t know why we would run the risk of not impeaching the man.&#8221; </p>
	</blockquote>

 
<div class="line"></div>

