<li><h2>Side Notes</h2>



<h3><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?id=1248" title="Permanent link to this article">Very interesting: Maps of War</a></h3>
	<p>Here&#8217;s a Flash film that provides a litte bit of <a href="http://www.mapsofwar.com/ind/imperial-history.html">history behind the Middle East</a> in 90 seconds.</p>
<small>Posted Oct 23</small>
<div class="line"></div><h3><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?id=1247" title="Permanent link to this article">Arborgeddon</a></h3>
	<p><a href="http://www.buffalorising.com/slideshows/arbordeggon/slideshow.html">A photo slideshow from BuffaloRising.com</a>. The photos give you an idea of both how leafy and Victorian Buffalo is. This storm still boggles my mind. Madison here is also very leafy and I cannot imagine how much this city would change if we lost that many limbs and trees. I guess I&#8217;ll find out when I visit Buffalo next spring/summer.</p>
<small>Posted Oct 17</small>
<div class="line"></div><h3><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?id=1246" title="Permanent link to this article">Updating Textpattern</a></h3>
	<p>If you notice a few weird things on the site it is because I&#8217;m updating the content management software. <a href="http://www.textpattern.com">Textpattern</a> is now at 4.0.4</p>
<small>Posted Oct 17</small>
<div class="line"></div><h3><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?id=1235" title="Permanent link to this article">RIP poor iPod</a></h3>
	<p>This poor person&#8217;s 4G iPod died <a href="http://flickr.com/photos/sabellachan/237798173/in/pool-tuawrigs/">so she decided to give it a funeral</a>. Having lost three, yes three, 4G iPods (Apple finally gave me an iPod Photo and it works great), I find this hilarious.</p>

 
<small>Posted Sep 10</small>
<div class="line"></div><h3><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?id=1225" title="Permanent link to this article">Dead Sea pottery?</a></h3>
	<p>Was the home of the Dead Sea Scrolls really a <a href="http://www.iht.com/articles/2006/08/16/healthscience/snqum.php">pottery factory</a>?</p>

 
<small>Posted Aug 16</small>
<div class="line"></div><h3><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?id=1223" title="Permanent link to this article">Here&#39;s a cat I could own...</a></h3>
	<p><a href="http://www.baekdal.com/future/intelliau/">Intelliau</a>, the world&#8217;s first robotic cat.</p>

 
<small>Posted Aug 12</small>
<div class="line"></div><h3><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?id=1222" title="Permanent link to this article">Something fishy...</a></h3>
	<p><a href="http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/06222/712245-55.stm">Gyotaku</a> at the Mount Lebanon Public Library.</p>

 
<small>Posted Aug 11</small>
<div class="line"></div><h3><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?id=1220" title="Permanent link to this article">Terror alert!</a></h3>
	<p>Have you noticed that we go on red alert, but it&#8217;s the Brits finding these plots? Had enough?</p>

 
<small>Posted Aug 10</small>
<div class="line"></div><h3><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?id=1217" title="Permanent link to this article">Fireworks in Madison</a></h3>
	<p>We have a small fireworks show each Regatta week on the Ohio River. It&#8217;s nothing extravegant, but it&#8217;s fun. You can watch the reflections on the river, but we were on our roof a couple blocks away.</p>
	<p>My favorite thing is listening to the explosions reverberate forever off our 400-foot bluffs. This year&#8217;s finale was punctuated by dozens of such explosions which made for a very satisfying ending.</p>

 
<small>Posted Jul  2</small>
<div class="line"></div><h3><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.php?id=1213" title="Permanent link to this article">Futurama autorama</a></h3>
	<p>I keep waiting for the cars of the future to show up, but so far, <a href="http://www.autoblog.com/2006/06/23/audi-r-zero-electric-sports-car/">this is as close as I&#8217;ve seen</a> .Too bad it is just a concept car.</p>

 
<small>Posted Jun 29</small>
